The **Inspect **panel allows to view more information on the status and properties of the selected job, and to download the job's request and response (if available), and the output of all intermediate tasks.

> **Note**

The option to save the outputs of all intermediate tasks for troubleshooting purposes is configured in the deployment phase. For more information, see: [On-Demand Workflow Resource Reference](/doxee-platform/docs/on-demand-workflow-resource-reference).

![](data:image/png;base64,)

> **Note**

For more information on the navigation bar and the common actions that can be performed on tables, see:

- [Doxee Platform 3 Navigation Bar](/doxee-platform/docs/doxee-platform-3-navigation-bar)

- [Doxee Platform 3 Common Functionalities](/doxee-platform/docs/doxee-platform-3-common-functionalities)

## Inspecting a job
**![](data:image/png;base64,)**

> **Tip**

Click on the **Jobs **link on the breadcrumb bar at the top to go back to the main page; for example:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

### Tasks
The **Tasks **table lists all individual processing tasks that have been executed by the job, and includes the following columns:

**Column**

**Description**

**Task**

ID of the task

**Started**

Date and time when the task was started

**Duration**

Total duration of the task execution

> **Note**

The duration is calculated according to the actual execution time, without considering the waiting time for resources or between scheduling and execution.

### Operations on jobs
**Icon**

**Action**

**Description**

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Download content**

Download the job's request and response (if available), and the output of all intermediate tasks.

> **Note**

For more information, see: [Doxee Platform On-Demand Jobs - Managing Jobs](/doxee-platform/docs/doxee-platform-on-demand-jobs-managing-jobs).
